Description: Neck and shoulder fragment of Late Wild Goat pottery oenochoe; ridge at base of neck. White-slipped. Slight remains of floral on neck; band below. Volute and palmette on shoulder, with fill of abbreviated tongues. Band of elongated maeanders on waist. Fired red-brown. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 434)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (Fikellura 76)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.615)
